//Which of these do you think might throw an exception that the compiler should care
  about?

 Things you want to do :                          What might go wrong:

✅Connect to a remote server                        The server is down
✅Access an array beyond its length                 Index out of bound
✅Display a window on the screen                    Display not supported
✅Retrieve data from a database                     Database connection issues, incorrect SQL queries
✅See if a text file is where you think it is       File not found, incorrect path
✅Create a new file                                 Incorrect path, permission etc.
✅Read a character from the command line            Input/output issue

